# Migrations

This directory contains Alembic database migration scripts for the Todo API.

## Structure

- `env.py`           — Alembic environment. Reads DATABASE_URL from .env at runtime.
- `script.py.mako`   — Template used to generate new migration files.
- `versions/`        — One file per migration, named with date + revision ID + description.

## Common commands

```bash
# Apply all pending migrations
alembic upgrade head

# Check which revision the database is at
alembic current

# Show full migration history
alembic history --verbose

# Roll back the last migration
alembic downgrade -1

# Generate a new migration after changing a model
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe_the_change"
```

## Notes

- The database URL is never hardcoded in alembic.ini. It is read from the
  DATABASE_URL environment variable (via .env) inside env.py.
- New migrations are generated automatically by diffing SQLAlchemy models
  against the live database schema (`--autogenerate`).
- Always review a generated migration file before applying it.
